Dear Community,

As our diversity and equity journey continues, Red Clay is joining the 21 Day Racial Equity & Social Justice Challenge
powered by United Way of Delaware (UWDE) and YWCA Delaware (YWCA). Join us and many Delawareans in a 21-day self-discovery journey.

This is your chance to build more effective social justice habits, particularly those dealing with issues of race, power, privilege, and leadership, by joining thousands of other Delawareans in a 21-day journey of self-discovery that you complete online, wherever you are comfortable.

https://deracialequitychallenge.org/

Congratulations to Conrad Schools of Science, Charter School of Wilmington, Thomas McKean High School and Delaware Military Academy for being honored by Delaware Interscholastic Athletic Association and receiving The Dale Farmer State Champions in Sportsmanship Award.

Delaware Military Academy
Thomas McKean High School
Conrad Schools of Science
Charter School of Wilmington

https://bit.ly/DIAASportsmanship
shared_text:
Delaware Interscholastic Athletic Association
July 27 at 2:18 PM ·

Sixteen Delaware schools are being honored for sportsmanship this week by the Delaware Interscholastic Athletic Association (DIAA).

The Dale Farmer State Champions in Sportsmanship award is presented annually to schools that have demonstrated a strong school community commitment to the educational nature of interscholastic athletics. This year's award was based on the fall and winter sport seasons; spring sports were cancelled due to COVID-19. The Board of Directors wanted to make sure that the students who worked hard during the year were honored. See link to check out the full story! Sanford School Sussex Technical High School The Tatnall School Thomas McKean High School

https://bit.ly/DIAASportsmanship

Dear Community,

We are looking at several options for the beginning of the 2020-21 school year, and we need your help. Your feedback is critical in informing these decisions.

We would like to hear from all Red Clay staff, parents/guardians, and students who will be entering grades 6 through 12 next year. Your confidential responses will help us understand your needs so we can best serve you.

Survey (English) - https://bit.ly/3iH8qty
Survey (Spanish) - https://bit.ly/3e6HAYC

Responses are needed by July 13, 2020. Teams will be meeting to review this data as part of the planning process.

post_text:
Congratulations to Kim Stock, who has been selected as Red Clay's 2020-21 Teacher of the Year! With 13 years of experience in education, Mrs. Stock teaches English language arts classes at Thomas McKean High School, where she works closely with students who are English learners.

Mrs. Stock brings a rich background of experience to Red Clay, with previous roles as a middle school English teacher in Lincoln, Nebraska, a language arts tutor and writer, a GED language arts instructor for adult learners, and the manager of a community-based learning center where she helped to increase the center's enrollment by over 100%.

In addition to her classroom duties, Mrs. Stock enjoys advocating for students as a proud Red Clay Diversity Champion.

"The most important job I have as a teacher," said Mrs. Stock, "is to teach my students for who they are and not who someone else thinks they are or thinks they should be."

If you have a mental health emergency, please call the Child Priority Response 24 Hour Crisis Line at 800-969-4357. For medical concerns, please contact your primary care provider or visit a Medical Aid Unit. If you have a question for your School-Based Health Center provider, please send a text message to 302-285-9661. You will receive a reply when texting this line during normal business hours 8am-4pm Monday through Friday within 24 hours.

Xfinity WiFi Free For Everyone

Comcast has opened free Xfinity wifi hotspots nationwide during this national emergency for the next 60 days. Anyone, not just Comcast customers, will be able to access the Internet via these hotspots.

Xfinity WiFi hotspots across the country will be available to anyone who needs them for free – including non-Xfinity Internet subscribers.

Once at a hotspot, consumers should select the “xfinitywifi” network name in the list of available hotspots, and then launch a browser.

View hotspots near you at www.xfinity.com/wifi

post_text: Meet Ryan Kennedy, VP of Marketing for Harvey Hanna. Leaders from Harvey Hanna started the Delaware KIDS Fund 12 years ago when they saw a need to help local children in distressed situations. With a focus on helping kids struggling with hunger and confidence, the Delaware KIDS Fund has provided hundreds of coats to help keep Red Clay students warm in the winter. Ryan and his team have also opened food pantries and basic needs closets in Red Clay elementary schools. Upon being inducted into the Red Clay Hall of Fame, Kennedy said, "this only just fires us up even more, and pushes us more, and inspires us more to get involved." Ryan hopes other businesses see what Harvey Hanna is doing and feel inspired to be #communitystrong.

The Delaware Division of Public Health has provided school districts with helpful information about the coronavirus. Although there are no confirmed cases in Red Clay schools or the State of Delaware, we want to be proactive in sharing this information with our families and our community.

The best precautions to take are the same ones recommended for avoiding colds and flu:

- Stay home if you are sick
- Cover your coughs and sneezes with tissues, or cough or sneeze into your inner elbow
- Wash your hands often
- Avoid touching eyes, nose or mouth
- Avoid contact with others who are sick

Anyone with concerns should contact their healthcare provider or visit https://dhss.delaware.gov/dhss/dph/index.html.

Delaware Division of Public Health - DPH

Thank you to the amazing Devon Still for an inspiring morning at the First State School!

A former professional athlete, entrepreneur, motivational speaker, and advocate for childhood cancer awareness, Devon stopped by and visited students and staff before delivering the keynote at the ChristianaCare Way awards ceremony.

Devon, we can't wait to have you back soon!

ChristianaCare

"It means so much to me that your school is dedicated to acceptance and inclusion," Special Olympic gold medalist Lucy Meyer told students and staff at Thomas McKean High School on January 17.

Joined by Senator Chris Coons, Meyer commended McKean, a 2019 Unified Champion Banner School, for its success in unified sports and its longstanding commitment to inclusivity.

As part of this inspiring event, principal Brian Mattix led a Q&A where students had an opportunity to learn more about Meyer, including how she overcame challenges earlier in her life to become a five-time gold medalist in swimming.

Thank you to Senator Coons, Lucy, Special Olympics Delaware, and McKean for this memorable day!

Team Lucy Meyer
U.S. Senator Chris Coons
Special Olympics Delaware

post_text:
Congratulations to Red Clay's own Daniel Lee and Atharva Shanbhag for winning the 2019 Congressional App Challenge! We are so proud to see these innovators team up and take their STEM skills from the classroom to the real world. Together they created the award-winning MapShot app, which is designed to help people alert their communities when they see violence.

Congresswoman Lisa Blunt Rochester stopped by the school lobby yesterday to congratulate the students in person, with Superintendent Green and school leaders from Cab Calloway School of the Arts and The Charter School of Wilmington.

As Delaware's winners of the Congressional App Challenge, Daniel and Atharva are headed to the #HouseofCode Capitol Hill Coding Exposition in D.C. and their app will also be featured in the U.S. Capitol, on House.gov, and on the Congressional App Challenge website.

Excellent job and good luck in D.C., Daniel and Atharva!

Delaware Department of Education (DDOE)
Cab Calloway School of the Arts
Charter School of Wilmington

Thank you to all of our amazing mentors, mentoring coordinators and partners who show up week after week to help Red Clay students to believe in themselves and be all they can be.

Red Clay Consolidated School District added 2 new photos from November 16, 2017.
December 27, 2019 at 12:09 PM ·

In Red Clay, we have a proud tradition of devoting the beginning of our school board meetings to publicly recognize those who have gone and above and beyond to achieve something great in Red Clay schools. These are people whose names and faces you might not know, but you should. People who are dedicating their lives to making their schools and communities the best places to learn and grow.

The Red Clay Education Foundation is seeking nominations for its 2020 Night of Stars gala. Click below to nominate someone who has made exceptional contributions to Red Clay, such as a current Red Clay student or graduate, a parent, former employee, or dedicated member of our community! https://bit.ly/2RZu3dI

Nominations will be accepted through January 2.

post_text:
Student-Athlete Recognition:

Congratulations to Conrad's Ny Whittlesey for winning Delaware Online's "Athlete of the Week." Over a three-game span last week, Whittlesey helped lead her team to 3 victories. She started the week by leading all scorers with a 20 point game and finished the week with an impressive feat where she tallied 18 points and 18 rebounds.

https://www.delawareonline.com/story/sports/high-school/2019/12/20/conrad-girls-basketball-delaware-online-athlete-week-vote-ny-whittlesey-she-got-game-classic/2708505001/

Henry C. Conrad Schools of Science
